{{refimprove|date=September 2018}}
The '''physiological density''' or '''real population density''' is the [[Population|number of people]] per unit area of [[arable land]].

A higher physiological density suggests that the available agricultural [[land]] is being used by more and may reach its output limit sooner than a country that has a lower physiological density.  [[Egypt#Demographics|Egypt]] is a notable example, with physiological density reaching that of Bangladesh, despite much desert.

